snippet.textDisplay:
Nate round 3, and edged round 5. Round 4 was pivotal and Connor took it. Looked like Nate was a little tired and the blood in his eyes bothered him enough to slow him down. Connor's boxing when everyone is 100% is a grade above Diaz. But Diaz is so tough and has enough cardio to soak up the damage and tire out his opponent's skill and reflexes.
I'm not sure there is a tougher fighter in the game than Diaz in terms of straight up taking damage and getting in his opponents face regardless of what they hit them with.
Connor showed he has the spirit of champion when he came back in the 4th and 5th after looking spent and battered in the 3rd.
snippet.textOriginal:
Nate round 3, and edged round 5.  Round 4 was pivotal and Connor took it.  Looked like Nate was a little tired and the blood in his eyes bothered him enough to slow him down.  Connor's boxing when everyone is 100% is a grade above Diaz.  But Diaz is so tough and has enough cardio to soak up the damage and tire out his opponent's skill and reflexes.
  I'm not sure there is a tougher fighter in the game than Diaz in terms of straight up taking damage and getting in his opponents face regardless of what they hit them with.
Connor showed he has the spirit of champion when he came back in the 4th and 5th after looking spent and battered in the 3rd.

snippet.textDisplay: Idk how Diaz didn’t win that fight. The judges were fucking blind. He out worked Conner and with exception of the first two rounds which were 1-1 Nate kept Connor on the retreat and in a close final round Nate was edging the win on the cage and sealed it with the leg sweep and ground and pound. They just didn’t like that Nate kept slapping McGregor and throwing the bird. Bro take a closer look at round 2! It’s a wash at best but Take out the two “knockdowns” and you see Nate wasn’t even hurt, just lost his feet from under him and that was the first minute. The back 3 minutes, Nate was dominating him and pretty much walked him down the rest of the fight with majority of the time having the DOMINANT POSITION and he  the 5th was edged out at the last moment with the 30 second leg sweep to ground and pound. If you’re talking about how bad Nate’s face looked you obviously don’t watch regularly. That’s scar tissue bro. Fight for 10 years against legends with an iron chin styled ya, your going to be a fighter who bleeds everywhere. Blood to the face is not an indicator of damage. Nate almost closed it in the 3rd and fourth until the bell saved Connors ass.
